The paper deals with versioning of resources on the Web, specifically in the context of Linked Data. It proposes a versioning mechanism that is fully based on HTTP and is congruent with the Architecture of the World Wide Web. This suggests that cs.WEB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Content Management Systems and Web Archives, which are relevant to cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of Linked Data and DBpedia suggests relevance to cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper proposes a framework for versioning, which could be considered a software engineering problem, indicating relevance to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
